{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-leptocoma-sperata", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-leptocoma-sperata", "name": "Purple-throated sunbird", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-genus-leptocoma", "name": "Leptocoma", "latinName": "Leptocoma", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Leptocoma（Leptocoma）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联6种鸟类，如Purple-rumped sunbird、Crimson-backed sunbird、Van Hasselt's sunbird等6种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 6, "x": -190.98, "y": 375.79, "z": 28.02}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-leptocoma-sperata", "name": "Purple-throated sunbird", "latinName": "Leptocoma sperata", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Purple-throated sunbird（Leptocoma sperata）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Purple-throated sunbird。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -523.17, "y": 3590.46, "z": 147.06}, {"id": "bird-purple-throated-sunbird-c0917cf3", "name": "Purple-throated sunbird", "englishName": "Purple-throated sunbird", "latinName": "Leptocoma sperata", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The purple-throated sunbird (Leptocoma sperata), is a species of bird in the family Nectariniidae. Its natural habitats are lowland tropical forests and tropical mangrove forests of Maratua and the Philippines. The Van Hasselt's sunbird was previously considered conspecific. Description and taxonomy EBird describes it as \"A very small bird of wooded areas from the lowlands to lower elevations in the mountains. Male has dark upperparts with a greenish crown and rump, a deep purple throat and upper chest, and a bright red lower chest and upper belly. In Sulu and west Mindanao birds, the red on the chest is replaced by yellow with an orange wash. Male is distinctive. Female resembles several other drab female sunbirds, but has a yellow brow and chest and a brown wing. Call is a sharp upslurred \"tsweep!\"\" In 1760 the French zoologist Mathurin Jacques Brisson included a description of the purple-throated sunbird in his Ornithologie based on a specimen collected in the Philippines. He used the French name Le grimpereau pourpré des Philippines and the Latin Certhia Philippensis Purpurea. Although Brisson coined Latin names, these do not conform to the binomial system and are not recognised by the International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature. When in 1766 the Swedish naturalist Carl Linnaeus updated his Systema Naturae for the twelfth edition, he added 240 species that had been previously described by Brisson. One of these was the purple-throated sunbird. Linnaeus included a brief description, coined the binomial name Certhia sperata and cited Brisson's work. Linnaeus specified the type location as the Philippines but this was subsequently restricted to Manila. The specific name sperata is Latin for \"bride\" or \"betrothed\". The species is now placed in the genus Leptocoma was introduced by the German ornithologist Jean Cabanis in 1850. Four subspecies are recognised: L. s. henkei (Meyer, AB, 1884) – north Luzon L. s. sperata (Linnaeus, 1766) – central and south Luzon, Polillo Island, Marinduque and Catanduanes (north Philippines) L. s. trochilus (Salomonsen, 1953) – west, central and south Philippines (except west and south Mindanao and Sulu Archipelago) L. s. juliae (Tweeddale, 1877) – west and south Mindanao and Sulu Archipelago The subspecies juliae is split under Handbook of the Birds of the World as Orange-lined sunbird. Ecology and behavior Feeds largely on nectar, although they will also take insects, especially when feeding young. Flight is fast and direct on their short wings. Most species can take nectar by hovering like a hummingbird, but usually perch to feed most of the time. Breeds from December to May. Only one nest has been described. This nest was attached to the tip of a fern and tear-drop shaped It was made of a tangle of dried leaves and stems and had a side entrance and contained 2 eggs. Habitat and conservation status Its natural habitats at tropical moist lowland primary forest and secondary forest, gardens and plantations mostly in the lowlands. The IUCN Red List has assessed this bird as least-concern species although it is poorly known. It is common across its range and seems to tolerate more disturbed habitats. References Rasmussen, P.C., and J.C. Anderton. 2005. Birds of South Asia. The Ripley guide. Volume 2: attributes and status. Smithsonian Institution and Lynx Edicions, Washington D.C. and Barcelona. External links Media related to Leptocoma sperata at Wikimedia Commons Data related to Leptocoma sperata at Wikispecies", "shortSummary": "The purple-throated sunbird (Leptocoma sperata), is a species of bird in the family Nectariniidae. Its natural habitats are lowland tropica…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Purple-throated_Sunbird_Palawan.jpg/960px-Purple-throated_Sunbird_Palawan.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-leptocoma", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-leptocoma-sperata", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-leptocoma", "species": "taxonomy-species-leptocoma-sperata"}, "expandable": true, "x": -523.17, "y": 3590.46, "z": 131.56}], "links": [{"key": "bird-purple-throated-sunbird-c0917cf3__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-leptocoma-sperata", "source": "bird-purple-throated-sunbird-c0917cf3", "target": "taxonomy-species-leptocoma-sperata", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-leptocoma-sperata__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-leptocoma", "source": "taxonomy-species-leptocoma-sperata", "target": "taxonomy-g